Package: google-android-cmdline-tools-%VER%-installer
Architecture: amd64 i386
Conflicts: ${cmdline-tools:Conflicts}
Replaces: ${cmdline-tools:Replaces}
Depends: default-jre-headless,
         google-android-build-tools,
         google-android-licenses (= ${source:Version}),
         ${googleAndroidInstallers:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Provides: ${cmdline-tools:Provides}
Homepage: https://developer.android.com/studio/command-line#tools-sdk
Description: Google's %PACKAGE_DISPLAY_NAME% (%VER%) Installer
 This package will download the Google's %PACKAGE_DISPLAY_NAME% (%VER%)
 package and unpacks it into Debian-friendly paths.
 .
 Google's %PACKAGE_DISPLAY_NAME% (%VER%) contains various tools for
 building and debugging Android apps. It is released concurrently with Android
 Studio and is installed in /usr/lib/android-sdk/cmdline-tools/<version>/bin/
 directory.
 .
 The tools shipped by this package are:
  apkanalyzer,
  avdmanager,
  lint,
  retrace,
  sdkmanager.
 .
 WARNING: Installing this Debian package causes
 %ZIPFILE% (%MB_SIZE% MB) to be downloaded
 from dl.google.com and/or from other suggested mirrors. The End User License
 Agreement of this binary package is available at developer.android.com.
